00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:05,750
Anyway, if that quack doctor gets caught by me, he's dead. I'll just—

374
00:36:05,750 --> 00:36:07,810
Leave it alone. Isn't he a doctor?

375
00:36:07,810 --> 00:36:10,610
It's a relief it's a misdiagnosis.

376
00:36:10,610 --> 00:36:13,030
I have an upset stomach and indigestion,

377
00:36:13,030 --> 00:36:15,620
because you eat ramyeon day in and day out. You shouldn't do that.

378
00:36:15,620 --> 00:36:19,760
If you cooked me a delicious meal, I wouldn't have gone out to eat.

379
00:36:43,650 --> 00:36:49,150
Running around and hanging out in some random neighborhood, you brat!

380
00:37:57,940 --> 00:38:00,170
Are you okay?

381
00:38:00,170 --> 00:38:02,610
I will be okay, right?

382
00:38:02,610 --> 00:38:08,130
When they threatened to have you deported, why didn't you just leave?

383
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:11,430
If you had left, they wouldn't have gone this far.

384
00:38:12,210 --> 00:38:14,390
Should I have?

385
00:38:16,170 --> 00:38:18,770
But I had to be sure.

386
00:38:18,770 --> 00:38:25,040
That they are going so far means I am getting closer to the truth.

387
00:38:26,150 --> 00:38:28,490
What's so important about the truth?

388
00:38:29,260 --> 00:38:32,670
What's so important about the past?

389
00:38:32,670 --> 00:38:36,110
Is it more important than your life or your future?

390
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:40,790
Just leave Korea.

391
00:38:40,790 --> 00:38:43,760
There are many people who forget everything and move on.

392
00:38:45,890 --> 00:38:48,500
I tried that.

393
00:38:48,500 --> 00:38:53,630
I ran away.  To the hospital.  To the battlefield.

394
00:38:54,550 --> 00:38:56,870
But that didn't work.

395
00:38:59,600 --> 00:39:02,180
Now I can't stop.

396
00:39:02,180 --> 00:39:04,710
I have no choice but to see the end of this.

397
00:39:08,070 --> 00:39:12,910
Miss Eugene.  Have you made a lot of mistakes?

398
00:39:12,910 --> 00:39:15,650
You said you were chased out because you made a mistake.

399
00:39:16,610 --> 00:39:19,200
Help me atone for it.

400
00:39:19,950 --> 00:39:23,510
So that a wrongly accused person doesn't die right in front of my eyes again.

401
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:34,260
Let's talk.

402
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:39,280
Accept help.  It's too hard to do it alone.

403
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:42,200
I came alone.

404
00:39:42,910 --> 00:39:44,880
Let's talk.

405
00:39:45,970 --> 00:39:49,030
What are you going to do? What can you do alone?

406
00:39:49,030 --> 00:39:51,250
Please trust me.

407
00:39:53,380 --> 00:39:57,540
If you go like this, you will get hurt.

408
00:40:02,890 --> 00:40:08,060
Everyone I meet dies, and now they are trying to kill me.

409
00:40:11,490 --> 00:40:14,020
From now on, it's my problem.

410
00:40:14,020 --> 00:40:17,740
- Why is that your problem? 
 - Detective Cha!

411
00:40:25,110 --> 00:40:27,360
You were using me, right?

412
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:37,030
At the detention center, then,

413
00:40:37,030 --> 00:40:39,400
and going so far as to use my anxiety about my mother,

414
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:42,820
did you plan on weakening my resolve from the beginning?

415
00:40:43,650 --> 00:40:46,950
Did you do that intentionally to make me bring you your Bible?

416
00:40:56,900 --> 00:40:58,490
Shoot.

417
00:41:04,130 --> 00:41:06,030
I said to shoot.

418
00:41:06,780 --> 00:41:09,040
You don't trust me anyway.

419
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:13,370
I said to shoot!

420
00:41:18,890 --> 00:41:20,870
Don't test me.

421
00:42:28,750 --> 00:42:31,010
Have you eaten?

422
00:42:55,950 --> 00:42:57,900
Mom.

423
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:03,160
Come in.

424
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:05,450
Come on in.

425
00:43:05,450 --> 00:43:08,160
Leave your shoes here.

426
00:43:16,630 --> 00:43:19,640
The room is a bit ...

427
00:43:21,290 --> 00:43:25,130
All Koreans live like this.

428
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:28,940
Now, let's see.

429
00:43:36,260 --> 00:43:39,400
 Certificate of Merit

430
00:43:50,780 --> 00:43:52,700
All right.  Try this.

431
00:43:54,200 --> 00:43:58,090
This should fit.  Put this on.

432
00:43:58,090 --> 00:43:59,740
And,

433
00:44:04,420 --> 00:44:06,210
don't be apologetic.

434
00:44:06,210 --> 00:44:08,430
Quickly change and come out.

435
00:44:25,740 --> 00:44:28,140
Go and take a seat.

436
00:44:29,150 --> 00:44:32,330
We've met before, right?

437
00:44:32,330 --> 00:44:35,660
Did I?  Me?

438
00:44:35,660 --> 00:44:39,740
Yes, I think I gave you directions at Hanmyeong University.

439
00:44:39,740 --> 00:44:41,820
Right?

440
00:44:41,820 --> 00:44:46,010
Well.  I've never been there.

441
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:49,240
You must have seen someone who looks like me.

442
00:44:49,240 --> 00:44:51,750
I think I am correct.

443
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:55,960
Why would I ever visit a university?

444
00:45:32,180 --> 00:45:35,780
It's not bad, so eat a lot.

445
00:45:35,780 --> 00:45:38,700
Thank you.  It's very delicious.

446
00:45:41,820 --> 00:45:47,320
But it hasn't rained. Is there a water leak in your house?

447
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:57,800
- On the ceiling... The-the bathroom in the apartment above is— Anyway... 
 - What?

448
00:45:57,800 --> 00:46:01,780
The floor became a sea of water at his house.

449
00:46:01,780 --> 00:46:03,860
Oh no...

450
00:46:04,920 --> 00:46:07,780
He will leave after a few days.

451
00:46:10,420 --> 00:46:14,370
Make yourself at home. Don't worry about us.

452
00:46:14,370 --> 00:46:15,290
I'm sorry.

453
00:46:15,290 --> 00:46:17,500
No need to be sorry.

454
00:46:21,460 --> 00:46:27,030
But, you two look so good together.

455
00:46:35,500 --> 00:46:38,290
- No. Not at all. 
 - What?

456
00:46:38,290 --> 00:46:42,030
Not at all.  It's not so, Mother.

457
00:46:42,030 --> 00:46:45,360
That's being very rude to the lady.

458
00:46:45,360 --> 00:46:47,940
Why?

459
00:46:47,940 --> 00:46:52,520
Eugene, he's not at all your type, right?

460
00:46:52,520 --> 00:46:54,120
What?

461
00:46:58,150 --> 00:47:00,450
I don't know.

462
00:47:00,530 --> 00:47:03,660
Mom, she has such high standards.

463
00:47:08,950 --> 00:47:16,050
But Miss, are you a police officer working with my Hwan?

464
00:47:20,930 --> 00:47:25,560
I'm not a police officer.  I'm a dispatcher.

465
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:27,360
Is that so?

466
00:47:28,590 --> 00:47:31,290
As long as you're not a police officer.

467
00:47:32,120 --> 00:47:35,690
I'm glad I didn't say anything wrong.

468
00:47:36,990 --> 00:47:39,310
- Mother. 
 - Hm?

469
00:47:46,380 --> 00:47:49,050
- Eat, Mother. 
 - I will.

470
00:47:49,050 --> 00:47:51,150
- Eat a lot. 
 - Thank you.

471
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:59,650
Head back home now.

472
00:47:59,650 --> 00:48:01,990
I'll take you as far as there.

473
00:48:05,050 --> 00:48:06,690
Earlier, that gun ...

474
00:48:06,690 --> 00:48:10,350
Oh, yes.  I took out the bullets.

475
00:48:10,350 --> 00:48:12,710
Just in case there is an accident.

476
00:48:15,710 --> 00:48:19,070
But will it be all right?

477
00:48:20,140 --> 00:48:24,670
For now, I will keep him at my home, but who knows when he'll run off or to where.

478
00:48:25,820 --> 00:48:27,810
Umm, Investigator.

479
00:48:31,050 --> 00:48:32,890
Lee Jung Yeop ...

480
00:48:34,910 --> 00:48:37,980
Are you saying he is Reporter Kim Hyo Gyeong's real brother?

481
00:48:41,690 --> 00:48:46,360
No wonder. I thought her interest in chimera was excessive.

482
00:48:47,700 --> 00:48:52,130
Should I tell Lee Jung Yeop?

483
00:48:52,930 --> 00:48:56,250
I'm sure he will try to meet her immediately.

484
00:48:56,250 --> 00:49:00,540
So for the time being I think it's better not to tell him until he is safe.

485
00:49:06,620 --> 00:49:11,430
Is this what happens when you look for your family?

486
00:49:31,030 --> 00:49:33,170
Is it okay to treat a guest like this?

487
00:49:33,170 --> 00:49:35,980
When you lose at rock-paper-scissors, accept it like a man.

488
00:49:35,980 --> 00:49:38,450
Let's play another game. If I'm not in this bed—

489
00:49:38,450 --> 00:49:42,110
Forget it.  I don't want to.

490
00:49:53,750 --> 00:49:58,940
They bought off the prosecution and controlled the media in order to instigate a murder.

491
00:49:58,940 --> 00:50:02,380
Why are the Seoryun people going this far?

492
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:07,650
There must be something they really fear.

493
00:50:07,650 --> 00:50:10,860
He seemed like a good person.

494
00:50:10,860 --> 00:50:13,730
- Who? 
 - Chairman Seo Hyeon Tae.

495
00:50:13,730 --> 00:50:15,230
I had a drink with him before.

496
00:50:15,230 --> 00:50:16,630
- You drank with him? 
 - Yes.

497
00:50:16,630 --> 00:50:19,760
- Just the two of you? 
 - Yes.

498
00:50:21,630 --> 00:50:26,220
Be careful. I think he was trying to get information out of you while drinking.

499
00:50:26,220 --> 00:50:29,310
What do you take me for?

500
00:50:29,310 --> 00:50:31,790
I didn't say much.

501
00:50:31,790 --> 00:50:36,170
He only asked about my mom and was concerned about me.

502
00:50:38,290 --> 00:50:41,010
Don't be fooled.

503
00:50:41,010 --> 00:50:46,530
Those people aren't the type who drink and open their hearts.

504
00:50:47,890 --> 00:50:51,170
Come to think of it you are a bit clueless—

505
00:50:51,250 --> 00:50:55,250
How should I say it? You are a bit naive.

506
00:50:56,110 --> 00:50:58,960
Later, you will be the only one hurt.

507
00:51:00,060 --> 00:51:05,350
Of course.  I'm Korea's best pushover.

508
00:51:05,350 --> 00:51:09,480
I'm giving a fugitive a place to sleep. If I get caught, I'll be done for.

509
00:51:09,480 --> 00:51:14,430
If you get caught, just say you caught me. Thanks to me, you'll make it to the top.

510
00:51:14,430 --> 00:51:16,570
I should.

511
00:51:27,090 --> 00:51:30,930
I have something I want to ask you.

512
00:51:30,930 --> 00:51:32,610
What is it?

513
00:51:33,830 --> 00:51:37,250
How would you feel if you had a sibling?

514
00:51:37,250 --> 00:51:40,170
What?  Out of the blue?

515
00:51:40,170 --> 00:51:44,340
